Scuttlebutt - a water barrel or butt that is scuttled with a hole so that water could be taken out to drink.  There is loitering around the scuttlebutt, it is the water cooler and gossip 
place of Haven.

Scuttle - a shallow open basket for carrying something such as grain or produce
a metal pail that has a bail and a sloped lip and is used for carrying coal
a small opening or hatchway in the deck of a ship large enough to admit a person and with a lid for covering it
a small hole in the side or bottom of a ship fitted with a covering or glazed
to cut a hole through the bottom, deck, or side
to sink or attempt to sink by making holes through the bottom
destroy, wreck
a quick shuffling pace
a short swift run
scurry
scuttling is performed to dispose of an abandoned, old, or captured vessel.  to prevent the vessel from navigation hazzards, as an act of self destruction to prevent the ship from being 
captured, or in the case of a vessel doing illegal activities.
deliberately sinking a ship by allowing water to flow into the hull.  
seacocks or hatches can be opened to the sea, these holes can be ripped into the hull with brute force or with explosives.  
a blockship to restrict navigation through a channel or within a harbor, to provide an artificial reef for divers and marine life, or to alter the flow of rivers.
